	"title": "En ville — Places & directions",
	"objective": "Locate places and give simple directions (A1: can ask for and give directions using a map or in the street).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: « à + le = au » and « il y a »",
		"body": "“To/at the” contracts: **à + le → au**, **à + les → aux** (but **à la** and **à l'** stay). So *je vais au marché* (to the market). **Il y a** = “there is / there are” (one phrase for both): *Il y a une gare ici.* Hindi यहाँ एक स्टेशन है works similarly — location word + है. Watch the contraction; learners often wrongly say ✗ *à le marché*."
	},
